"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1132550","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-06-25","<p>This Government is committed to boosting housing supply and to build more affordable homes, including for social rent. Housing Infrastructure Fund grant funding will support local authorities to develop ambitious plans to meet their area’s affordable housing need. These will be agreed through the usual planning process.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2019-06-25T11:26:35.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1132550/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1132550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1132550/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-06-17","Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what proportion of the homes being unlocked by the Housing Infrastructure Fund are expected to be affordable homes, and what proportion of those affordable homes are expected to be social rented homes.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","265607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1132551","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-06-24","<p>I refer my Hon Friend to the reply previously given on 8 April 2019 to PQ 238630.</p><p> </p><p>Our assessments of emissions of pollutants from domestic combustion sources use a range of data but are based on established international reporting. The range of fuels and appliances used in the UK is large and emissions from each combination vary greatly depending on how the appliance is operated.</p><p> </p><p>Any publicly available resources we have used to inform our analysis of the proposals in the consultation will be made available with the Government response.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","265472","2019-06-24T12:58:17.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1132551/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1132551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1132551/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-06-17","Solid Fuels: Heating","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to his Department's consultation on cleaner domestic burning of solid fuels and wood in England, if he will place in the Library copies of reports and datasets on the gluing agents used in the manufacture of smokeless briquettes and the toxic pollutants these gluing agents release when burnt on open domestic fires being considered in that consultation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","265473"
