"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131625","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-06-21","<p>The Ministry of Justice is continuing discussions with its Suppliers in relation to the outage. Due to the ongoing nature of these discussions it is not possible to provide any information pertaining to the quantification of costs, at this time.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2019-06-21T13:30:19.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131625/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1131625/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-06-12","Courts and Probation: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the cost to the public purse of IT systems failures in probation services and the courts in January 2019.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","263817"
